      "name": "Class III centrifugal VAD applicability domain",
      "description": "Applicability is restricted to continuous-flow centrifugal blood pumps operating as long-term ventricular assist devices in adult patients (BSA 1.5–2.2 m²). The model is applicable only when blood viscosity falls within 2.7–4.5 mPa·s (hematocrit 30–45%), inlet flow rates are 3–6 L/min, and rotational speed is 2400–3200 RPM. Extrapolation beyond these bounds, or application to pulsatile-flow or axial-flow devices, is explicitly excluded."
    },
