      },
      "rationale": "Code verification was performed using the Method of Manufactured Solutions (MMS) applied to the incompressible Navier-Stokes equations coupled with the Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power law. Three spatial refinement levels (coarse 4M, medium 8M, fine 16M cells) yielded observed spatial order of accuracy of 1.94 against the formal order of 2.0 — a 3% deviation well within the 10% acceptance threshold. Temporal verification using a sinusoidal manufactured solution confirmed second-order accuracy (observed 1.98). Iterative convergence was demonstrated to residuals below 1×10⁻⁶ for all equations. These results satisfy ASME V&V 40 Gradation 4 numerical code verification for MRL 5."
