      "rationale": "Grid convergence was assessed using Richardson extrapolation across three systematically refined polyhedral meshes (8M, 14M, and 22M cells; refinement ratio 1.32). The Grid Convergence Index (GCI) for the primary quantity of interest — normalized hemolysis index — is 0.8%, well below the 2% acceptance threshold. Secondary QoI pressure rise GCI is 1.1%. Wall y⁺ values are ≤ 0.87 on all blood-contacting surfaces, ensuring the viscous sublayer is fully resolved without wall functions. The achieved level of 5 reflects the exceptionally low GCI and the fully-resolved near-wall treatment, exceeding the Gradation 4 requirement for MRL 5."
