      "rationale": "Experimental validation tests were conducted at the FDA's Division of Applied Mechanics using anticoagulated porcine blood (hematocrit 38±2%) at all five operating points spanning the clinical duty cycle. Flow rates were measured with a Coriolis mass flowmeter (uncertainty ±1.4%), rotational speed with an optical tachometer (±0.3%), and blood viscosity with a cone-and-plate viscometer (±2.1%). All uncertainties are within acceptance thresholds. Temperature was maintained at 37±0.3 °C. The achieved Gradation 4 reflects the rigorous characterization of test boundary conditions with full uncertainty budgets, exceeding the Gradation 3 requirement."
