      },
      "rationale": "The SST k-ω turbulence model was selected based on its demonstrated superior performance in adverse pressure gradient and rotating machinery flows, as documented in five peer-reviewed publications on centrifugal blood pump CFD. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model was chosen over the Zhang model based on a comparative study at all five operating points; the two models agreed to within 8% on NIH at four of five points, with the largest discrepancy at the highest speed condition (18%). The sensitivity of NIH to turbulence model choice (SST k-ω vs. realizable k-ε) was quantified at ±12%, which is within the accepted uncertainty budget. Model form uncertainty is explicitly included in the Monte Carlo UQ. These assessments satisfy Gradation 4 model form requirements."
