      },
      "rationale": "Eleven uncertain model input parameters were identified: inlet flow rate, rotational speed, blood viscosity (power-law index and consistency), hemolysis model constants (C, α, β), inlet turbulence intensity, wall roughness, and pump geometric tolerances (3 parameters). Probability distributions were characterized from experimental measurement uncertainty reports and published literature. A 1000-sample Latin Hypercube Monte Carlo was performed, propagating all 11 inputs simultaneously. The 95% confidence interval on NIH ranges from ±8% to ±21% across the five operating points, with the largest uncertainty at the highest speed condition. All input distributions and Monte Carlo results are archived in the UQ dataset. These results satisfy Gradation 4 model input requirements for MRL 5."
