      "rationale": "Three independent experimental replicates were performed at each of the five operating points, yielding 15 total hemolysis tests. Fresh anticoagulated porcine blood was used for each replicate; each sample was characterized for hematocrit (38±2%), viscosity (3.4±0.2 mPa·s at 37°C), and baseline plasma-free hemoglobin (pfHb ≤ 5 mg/dL confirmed for all samples). Between-replicate coefficient of variation on NIH ranged from 4.2% to 8.7%, consistent with published inter-test variability for porcine blood hemolysis studies. The three-replicate design provides sufficient statistical power to detect a 15% change in NIH with 80% power. These results satisfy Gradation 3 test sample requirements."
