      },
      "rationale": "CFD boundary conditions were set to the experimentally measured values (not nominal setpoints) for each replicate at each operating point. Residual mismatches between CFD inputs and experimental measurements are ≤ 0.8% for flow rate and ≤ 0.2% for rotational speed — both within measurement uncertainty bounds. The sensitivity of NIH to these residual mismatches was estimated by perturbing boundary conditions by the mismatch magnitude: the resulting NIH change is ≤ 1.5% at all operating points, negligible relative to the overall uncertainty budget. Blood viscosity in CFD was set using the measured power-law parameters from each blood sample's rheometry characterization. This direct correspondence between experimental and computational inputs satisfies Gradation 4 equivalency requirements for MRL 5."
